Interface PartialFunction<F,T>

  • Type Parameters:
    F - the type of the function input
    T - the type of the function output
    All Superinterfaces:
    Function<F,T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ForwardingPartialFunction

    public interface PartialFunction<F,T>
extends Function<F,T>
    A partial function is a unary function where the domain does not include all values of the source type.

    Andres Rodriguez
